docs.snippet: The Uruguayan people have again lived up to their high reputation for political maturity and liberty. In a remarkable general election they turned out in great numbers; voted to change the executive branch of their Government from the cumbersome...
docs.lead_paragraph: The Uruguayan people have again lived up to their high reputation for political maturity and liberty. In a remarkable general election they turned out in great numbers; voted to change the executive branch of their Government from the cumbersome Swiss-type National Council to a President; picked an entirely new Senate and Chamber of Deputies and filled all local government posts. It was an election that made New York State's seem simple.
